      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 299: `onPushReceived()` increments `activePushCount` before doing operations that can throw, including the synchronous `setAccountsActive(..., awaitCompletion \u003d true)` call. If that call throws, the caller\u0027s `finally` still calls `onPushProcessed()`, but no native push was dispatched and the release timer/subscription setup below may not have been armed. Wrap the setup so the count is decremented on setup failure or move the increment after the non-recoverable setup has completed. For example:\n```suggestion\nfun onPushReceived() \u003d synchronized(pushStateLock) {\n    cancelIdleShutdown()\n    var counted \u003d false\n    try {\n        activePushCount.incrementAndGet()\n        counted \u003d true\n        ...\n        if (daemon.isStarted) {\n            mAccountService.setAccountsActive(true, forceAll \u003d false, awaitCompletion \u003d true)\n        }\n        ...\n    } catch (e: Exception) {\n        if (counted) activePushCount.decrementAndGet()\n        throw e\n    }\n}\n```",
