      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 353: The push hold can be kept alive indefinitely if `onPushProcessed()` is never reached after `onPushReceived()` increments `activePushCount` (for example if `onMessageReceived()` blocks, the coroutine is cancelled, or another future caller fails between the two calls). In that state `releasePushHold()` always defers, `idleShutdownRunnable` always returns because `activePushCount \u003e 0`, and account/network shutdown is disabled for the rest of the process lifetime. Make the max-window timeout authoritative: after the maximum window expires, release the wake/FGS hold and reset or expire stale in-flight push state instead of re-posting forever. For example:\n```suggestion\nprivate fun releasePushHold(force: Boolean \u003d false) \u003d synchronized(pushStateLock) {\n    if (!force \u0026\u0026 activePushCount.get() \u003e 0) {\n        Log.d(TAG, \"Push: still ${activePushCount.get()} in flight, deferring release\")\n        pushReleaseHandler.postDelayed({ releasePushHold(force \u003d true) }, pushMaxWindowMs)\n        return\n    }\n    if (force \u0026\u0026 activePushCount.get() \u003e 0) {\n        Log.w(TAG, \"Push: forcing release with ${activePushCount.get()} stale dispatch(es)\")\n        activePushCount.set(0)\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\nAlternatively track per-push deadlines/tokens so only stale pushes are expired.",
